import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="X", y="Y", data=data)
    ax.set_title("What is the correlation between X and Y?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['X'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X-Y'] = data['X'] - data['Y']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X-Y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['X-Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['X-Y'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['X-Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['X-Y'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X-Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('X-Y')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Series'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Series'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Series'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='Series', y='X', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of X over time (Series)?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('X')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
